# Story 3.2: Color-Code Markers by Status

## Story Metadata
- **Epic:** 3 - Map & Fleet Visualization
- **Status:** done
- **Implemented:** 2025-12-28
- **Session:** SESSION-004

## User Story
As **Diana (Dispatcher)**,
I want **markers color-coded by train status**,
So that **I can instantly identify available vs in-maintenance trains**.

## Acceptance Criteria

| AC | Criteria | Status |
|----|----------|--------|
| AC1 | Available trains shown in green | PASS |
| AC2 | In-service trains shown in blue | PASS |
| AC3 | In-maintenance trains shown in red | PASS |
| AC4 | Legend explains colors | PASS |

## Implementation Details

### Color Scheme
```typescript
const statusColors = {
  available: '#22c55e',  // Green
  'in-service': '#3b82f6', // Blue
  maintenance: '#ef4444',  // Red
  unfit: '#6b7280'  // Gray
};
```

### Legend Component
- Fixed position bottom-left
- Shows all status colors with labels
- Toggle visibility option

